text: Raszów () is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Kamienna Góra, within Kamienna Góra County, Lower Silesian Voivodeship, in south-western Poland. Prior to 1945 it was in Germany. It lies approximately west of Kamienna Góra and south-west of the regional capital Wrocław. ==References== Category:Villages in Kamienna Góra County
title: Raszów, Kamienna Góra County
